pros:
- Great benefits and salary for an NGO;
- flexible hours and work arrangements;
- meaningful work;
- lots of opportunities for learning (monetary help when taking courses, workshops,  a lot of competent people to learn from)
- lots of room for lateral growth

cons:
- Bad change management practices led to unsatisfied staff and low productivity during much needed albeit badly planned restructures;
- A lot of investment into marketing without having a good strategy in place led to a lot of frustration among staff who wanted to do good innovative work that didn't fit into a strategy
- Not a lot of room for vertical growth if you're not super Christian
